### Jobs API - Create and Manage Jobs (LOCAL DEVELOPMENT)
# Local development URL: http://localhost:8000/api/v1
#
# This file contains examples for:
# - Creating jobs (async and sync modes)
# - Creating jobs WITH DESTINATIONS (Cognee GraphRAG, HippoRAG Multi-Hop)
# - Getting job status and results
# - Listing jobs with filters
# - Cancelling jobs
# - Retrying failed jobs
#
# NEW: Destinations allow routing processed documents to GraphRAG systems:
# - cognee_local: Knowledge graph with Neo4j (entity extraction, graph search)
# - hipporag: Multi-hop retrieval with PageRank (complex reasoning)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@apiKey = your-api-key


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. CREATE JOBS (Basic - Standard Processing)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Create Job - PDF Document (Async Mode)
# Submit a new PDF ingestion job with async processing
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/sample-text.pdf",
  "file_name": "sample-text.pdf",
  "mime_type": "application/pdf",
  "mode": "async",
  "priority": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "pdf-text-extraction"
  }
}

### Create Job - Scanned PDF with OCR
# Submit a job requiring OCR processing for scanned documents
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/sample-scanned.pdf",
  "file_name": "sample-scanned.pdf",
  "mime_type": "application/pdf",
  "mode": "async",
  "priority": 3,
  "options": {
    "force_ocr": true,
    "ocr_language": "eng"
  },
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "pdf-ocr-extraction"
  }
}

### Create Job - Office Document (Word)
# Submit a Word document for processing
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/sample.docx",
  "file_name": "sample.docx",
  "mime_type": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document",
  "mode": "async",
  "priority": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "word-document"
  }
}

### Create Job - Excel Spreadsheet
# Submit an Excel spreadsheet for processing
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/sample.xlsx",
  "file_name": "sample.xlsx",
  "mime_type": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet",
  "mode": "async",
  "priority": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "excel-spreadsheet"
  }
}

### Create Job - Sync Mode (Immediate Processing)
# Submit a job for synchronous processing (waits for completion)
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/sample-text.pdf",
  "file_name": "sample-text.pdf",
  "mime_type": "application/pdf",
  "mode": "sync",
  "priority": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "sync-processing"
  }
}


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. CREATE JOBS WITH DESTINATIONS (GraphRAG Evolution)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 
# DESTINATIONS allow routing processed documents to specialized GraphRAG systems.
# Each destination type provides different capabilities:
#
# ┌─────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │ Destination     │ Capabilities                                                │
# ├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
# │ cognee_local    │ Knowledge graph (Neo4j) + Entity extraction + Graph search │
# │ hipporag        │ Multi-hop retrieval + PageRank + Complex reasoning         │
# └─────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
# You can specify multiple destinations to route data to multiple systems.
# The pipeline will process the document once and send results to all destinations.

### Create Job with Cognee Destination (Knowledge Graph)
# Route processed document to Cognee for knowledge graph construction.
# Cognee extracts entities and relationships, storing them in Neo4j.
# After processing, query via: POST /cognee/search
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/technical-doc.pdf",
  "file_name": "technical-doc.pdf",
  "mime_type": "application/pdf",
  "mode": "async",
  "destinations": [
    {
      "type": "cognee_local",
      "config": {
        "dataset_id": "default",
        "graph_name": "default",
        "extract_entities": true,
        "extract_relationships": true
      }
    }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "cognee-graphrag-ingestion",
    "description": "Knowledge graph construction with entity extraction"
  }
}

### Create Job with HippoRAG Destination (Multi-Hop RAG)
# Route processed document to HippoRAG for multi-hop retrieval indexing.
# HippoRAG uses Personalized PageRank for complex reasoning queries.
# After processing, query via: POST /hipporag/retrieve or POST /hipporag/qa
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/research-paper.pdf",
  "file_name": "research-paper.pdf",
  "mime_type": "application/pdf",
  "mode": "async",
  "destinations": [
    {
      "type": "hipporag",
      "config": {
        "dataset_id": "default"
      }
    }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "hipporag-multi-hop-ingestion",
    "description": "Multi-hop retrieval indexing for complex queries"
  }
}

### Create Job with Multiple Destinations (Cognee + HippoRAG)
# Route processed document to BOTH Cognee AND HippoRAG simultaneously.
# This provides both knowledge graph capabilities AND multi-hop retrieval.
# Useful when you need both entity relationships AND complex reasoning.
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/comprehensive-doc.pdf",
  "file_name": "comprehensive-doc.pdf",
  "mime_type": "application/pdf",
  "mode": "async",
  "destinations": [
    {
      "type": "cognee_local",
      "config": {
        "dataset_id": "default",
        "graph_name": "default",
        "extract_entities": true,
        "extract_relationships": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "hipporag",
      "config": {
        "dataset_id": "default"
      }
    }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "test_case": "multi-destination-graphrag",
    "description": "Full GraphRAG pipeline with Cognee KG + HippoRAG multi-hop"
  }
}

### Create Job with Destinations and Custom Filters
# Route only specific content types to destinations using filters.
# Filters can match on source_type, metadata fields, etc.
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "source_type": "upload",
  "source_uri": "/uploads/knowledge-base.pdf",
  "file_name": "knowledge-base.pdf",
  "mime_type": "application/pdf",
  "mode": "async",
  "destinations": [
    {
      "type": "cognee_local",
      "config": {
        "dataset_id": "kb-graph",
        "graph_name": "knowledge-base"
      },
      "filters": {
        "source_type": "pdf"
      },
      "enabled": true
    }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "source": "local-test",
    "category": "knowledge-base",
    "test_case": "filtered-destination-routing"
  }
}


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3. GET JOB STATUS AND RESULTS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get Job Status
# Retrieve detailed information about a specific job
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### Get Job Result
# Retrieve the processed output of a completed job
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}/result
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 4. LIST JOBS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### List Jobs (Default Pagination)
# Get all jobs with default pagination settings
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### List Jobs with Status Filter (Pending)
# Filter jobs by pending status
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs?status=pending&limit=10
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### List Jobs with Status Filter (Completed)
# Filter jobs by completed status
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs?status=completed&limit=10
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### List Jobs with Date Range Filter
# Filter jobs by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs?date_from=2024-01-01&date_to=2024-12-31&limit=50
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### List Jobs with Source Type Filter
# Filter jobs by source type
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs?source_type=upload&limit=10
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### List Jobs with Pagination
# Paginated list of jobs
GET {{baseUrl}}/jobs?page=1&limit=5
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 5. JOB MANAGEMENT
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Cancel Job
# Cancel a pending or running job
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

### Retry Failed Job
# Retry a job that has failed or been sent to DLQ
POST {{baseUrl}}/jobs/{{jobId}}/retry
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

{
  "force_parser": "azure_ocr",
  "priority": 10
}

###
